"slug": "phillip-brits",
"name": "Phillip Brits",
"photo": "assets/images/artists/phillip-brits.jpg",
"bio": "b. 1966\n\nJohannesburg\n\nPhillip Brits studied under his father, B. E. Brits and Alda Biljon, mastering the art of painting.\n\nHe is famous for his intricate style and impressionistic landscapes, locally and abroad. His most well-known works capture the beauty of the town of Arniston, with its white beach cottages and fishing boats. His artworks also capture village scenes and country lanes.\n\nBrits’ work has been exhibited at local municipalities and embassies, and sold to local and international art collectors.",
