"name": "Riaan Van Der Merwe",
"photo": "assets/images/artists/riaan-van-der-merwe.jpg",
"bio": "b. 1976\n\nRiaan was taught painting, sculpting and drawing by his grandmother Ellen Botha, who schooled him in the style of the old masters.\n\nHe is influenced by I by Caravaggio, Renoir and Van Gogh, and is well known for his portraits. Riaan has painted large 2 meter canvases of faces which draw attention. He applies paint in an impasto style with knife, brush or even using his hands.\n\nHis work is highly acclaimed and he has been awarded prizes for his portraits.",
